						<summary>

						<p>This is a label inscription in three lines. The writing is of the 10th Century A.D. It mentions Tirutturutti-Nam[bi] Śrīkaṇṭhar and Śivachara[ṇa]śēkharaṉ. Close to this is a sculpture representing a <hi rend="italic">liṅga</hi>, a worshipper, an attendant and a lampstand.</p>						

